              "      }\n",

              "\n",
              "        async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "          const element = document.querySelector('#df-40b58257-6c5e-4073-904b-3e571a912b86');\n",
              "          const dataTable =\n",
              "            await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                     [key], {});\n",
              "          if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "          const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "            '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "            + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "          element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "          dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "          await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "          const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "          docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "          element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "        }\n",
              "      </script>\n",
              "    </div>\n",
              "  </div>\n"
            ]
          },

              "        async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "          const element = document.querySelector('#df-54202bee-a5f6-4a78-89eb-0d175f8d9915');\n",
              "          const dataTable =\n",
              "            await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                     [key], {});\n",
              "          if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "          const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "            '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "            + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "          element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "          dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "          await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "          const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "          docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "          element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "        }\n",
              "      </script>\n",
              "    </div>\n",
              "  </div>\n"
            ]

        "\n",
        "\n",
        "1.Production Planning: Analyze the quantity of products produced and sold over time to optimize production planning and resource allocation."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "8Lmw1ToBjlCx"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "# Convert 'Date' column to datetime type\n",
        "df['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Date'])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Group by date and calculate sum of 'Quantity Sold' and 'Quantity Produced'\n",
        "sales_per_date = df.groupby('Date')['Quantity Sold (liters/kg)'].sum()\n",
        "production_per_date = df.groupby('Date')['Quantity (liters/kg)'].sum()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Plotting\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
        "plt.plot(sales_per_date.index, sales_per_date, label='Quantity Sold')\n",
        "plt.plot(production_per_date.index, production_per_date, label='Quantity Produced')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Date')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Quantity')\n",
        "plt.title('Production and Sales Over Time')\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.show()\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",

        "df1=df.sample(50)\n"
      ],

      "outputs": []

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "data=pd.DataFrame(df1)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "FkZI9xUjO4PA"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "samplefty = pd.DataFrame(data)\n",
        "samplefty['Production Date'] = pd.to_datetime(samplefty['Production Date'])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Group by date and calculate sum of 'Quantity Sold' and 'Price per Unit (sold)'\n",
        "sales_per_date = samplefty.groupby('Production Date')['Quantity Sold (liters/kg)'].sum()\n",
        "price_per_date = samplefty.groupby('Production Date')['Price per Unit (sold)'].mean()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Plotting\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
        "plt.plot(sales_per_date.index, sales_per_date, label='Quantity Sold')\n",
        "plt.plot(price_per_date.index, price_per_date, label='Price per Unit')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Production Date')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Quantity / Price')\n",
        "plt.title('Quantity Sold and Price per Unit Over Time')\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.show()\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {

        "5.\tProduct Shelf Life and Expiry: Track product shelf life and expiration dates to ensure timely sales and avoid wastage."

      "metadata": {
        "id": "o4_U66X24jyx"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "6.\tProduct Pricing Strategy: Analyze product pricing and its impact on sales volume and revenue generation."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "UwmdE0e84-6o"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "df['Revenue_High_Price'] = df['Quantity Sold (liters/kg)'] * df['Price per Unit (sold)'] * 1.1\n",
        "df['Revenue_Low_Price'] = df['Quantity Sold (liters/kg)'] * df['Price per Unit (sold)'] * 0.9\n",
        "revenue_high_price = df.groupby('Date')['Revenue_High_Price'].sum()\n",
        "revenue_low_price = df.groupby('Date')['Revenue_Low_Price'].sum()\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
        "plt.plot(revenue_per_date.index, revenue_per_date, label='Original Price')\n",
        "plt.plot(revenue_high_price.index, revenue_high_price, label='High Price')\n",
        "plt.plot(revenue_low_price.index, revenue_low_price, label='Low Price')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Date')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Revenue')\n",
        "plt.title('Revenue with Different Pricing Scenarios')\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {

    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Prediction using TimeSeries"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "_QTSYvx5B4qA"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from statsmodels.tsa.statespace.sarimax import SARIMAX\n",
        "from datetime import timedelta\n",
        "from statsmodels.tsa.arima_model import ARMA\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "df['Production Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Production Date'])\n",
        "df = df.groupby('Production Date')[['Quantity Sold (liters/kg)', 'Price per Unit (sold)']].sum()\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "regular_frequency = 'MS'\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "df = df.resample(regular_frequency).sum()\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "train_size = int(len(df) * 0.8)\n",
        "train_data = df.iloc[:train_size]\n",
        "test_data = df.iloc[train_size:]\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "sarima_quantity = SARIMAX(train_data['Quantity Sold (liters/kg)'],\n",
        "                          order=(1, 1, 1),\n",
        "                          seasonal_order=(1, 1, 1, 12))\n",
        "sarima_quantity_fit = sarima_quantity.fit(disp=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "forecast_quantity = sarima_quantity_fit.get_forecast(steps=len(test_data))\n",
        "forecast_quantity_index = pd.date_range(start=train_data.index[-1], periods=len(test_data)+1, freq='M')[1:]\n",
        "forecast_quantity = pd.Series(forecast_quantity.predicted_mean.values, index=forecast_quantity_index)\n",
        "\n",
        "sarima_quantity = SARIMAX(train_data['Quantity Sold (liters/kg)'],\n",
        "                          order=(1, 1, 1),\n",
        "                          seasonal_order=(1, 0, 1, 12),\n",
        "                          enforce_stationarity=False,\n",
        "                          enforce_invertibility=False)\n",
        "sarima_quantity_fit = sarima_quantity.fit(disp=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "window_size = 3\n",
        "moving_avg_price = train_data['Price per Unit (sold)'].rolling(window=window_size).mean()\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "forecast_price = moving_avg_price.iloc[-1]  # Use the last moving average value as the forecast\n",
        "forecast_price_index = pd.date_range(start=train_data.index[-1], periods=len(test_data)+1, freq='M')[1:]\n",
        "forecast_price = pd.Series([forecast_price] * len(forecast_price_index), index=forecast_price_index)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.subplot(2, 1, 1)\n",
        "plt.plot(train_data.index, train_data['Quantity Sold (liters/kg)'], label='Train Data')\n",
        "plt.plot(test_data.index, test_data['Quantity Sold (liters/kg)'], label='Test Data')\n",
        "plt.plot(forecast_quantity.index, forecast_quantity.values, label='Forecast')\n",
        "plt.title('Quantity Sold Forecast')\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.subplot(2, 1, 2)\n",
        "plt.plot(train_data.index, train_data['Price per Unit (sold)'], label='Train Data')\n",
        "plt.plot(test_data.index, test_data['Price per Unit (sold)'], label='Test Data')\n",
        "plt.plot(forecast_price.index, forecast_price.values, label='Forecast')\n",
        "plt.title('Price per Unit Forecast')\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 637
        },
        "id": "J37dlRPM9Mib",
        "outputId": "c0200240-588f-493c-8caa-ec9ad1f94864"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stderr",
          "text": [
            "/usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages/statsmodels/tsa/statespace/sarimax.py:866: UserWarning: Too few observations to estimate starting parameters for seasonal ARMA. All parameters except for variances will be set to zeros.\n",
            "  warn('Too few observations to estimate starting parameters%s.'\n"
          ]
        },
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 1200x600 with 2 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.metrics import mean_absolute_error, mean_squared_error\n",
        "\n",
        "mae_quantity = mean_absolute_error(test_data['Quantity Sold (liters/kg)'], forecast_quantity)\n",
        "mse_quantity = mean_squared_error(test_data['Quantity Sold (liters/kg)'], forecast_quantity)\n",
        "rmse_quantity = np.sqrt(mse_quantity)\n",
        "\n",
        "mae_price = mean_absolute_error(test_data['Price per Unit (sold)'], forecast_price)\n",
